5:
Damn... Mighty fine view, eh? Just 
when I thought I'd seen it all.
7:
Still so many sights to see, skills to 
master... 
Enough adventure for a lifetime.
16:
Well, if it ain't the champion himself! 
Heh... I owe you one fer earlier, friend.
18:
But to answer your question, I'm as fit 
as a fiddle—just drank a li'l too much 
water, is all.
23:
Yes, well... you were swelled up 
something awful when we found you.
28:
Hah-hah-hah! I'll admit, takin' on all 
'em sea monsters on my own wasn't 
one of my best ideas.
31:
Just means I've got a rematch on the 
horizon.
33:
Surely you've someone you'd like to 
take another shot at, right?
39: Yes... I do have a score I need to settle.
42:
It's not one I can laugh about, 
however.
45:
By the way... How come you never 
doubted my true identity?
48:
There are some things y' learn with 
age... One good look into yer eyes was 
all I needed t' understand.
50:
That... and yer distaste for yer current 
form.
58: Taiga, could ask a favor of you?
62:
Sure thing. 
If it's within my power, o' course.
71:
Don't let yer emotions get ahead of 
you. Again!
80:
No, no! Your spirit and your blade 
must be one and the same!
85:
Don't let my emotions get ahead... 
but put my spirit into it? Can you 
explain?
88:
You youngsters and your explanations... 
Save the thinkin' fer after you put your 
sword down—
now's the time for FEELIN'!
92:
Much too labored, Alk. 
Relax your shoulders... Imagine the 
blade as an extension of your very 
self.
94:
When you swing, imagine having 
already sliced through your target.
100:
There y' go! Now, this applies t' all 
types o' weapons, not only swords! 
Very sage advice, champion.
103:
Not at all. I was merely supplementing 
your instruction, Taiga.
107:
Listen here, sonny... Pay attention to 
the timing of yer steps.
112:
No, no! You need to put yer foot down 
harder!
124:
Exactly. Now let's see those planters 
planted!
128:
Wait, what am I planting again? 
Like this?
134:
No, no! You've barely put your foot to 
the ground!
138:
Use all the might you can muster, 
but make sure to start from your hips.
141:
Exactly! And don't forget about yer 
knees, too.
149:
You wouldn't want for them to lock, 
would you?
153:
Well said, champion. The boy still 
needs to get his fundamentals in 
order.
157:
Good eye, Taiga. If we can't solidify his 
fundamentals, he won't have anything 
to build upon.
166:
Oh, nothing... I'm just amazed at how 
you two seem to understand each 
other so well.
169:
Call it mutual understanding earned 
through years of experience.
173:
Awesome... Master! Teach me how to 
do that thing with the sword again!
178:
"That thing"? Yer gonna have to be 
more specific!
